      "message": "Good question.\n\nI believe the way I\u0027ve written it:\n* project B\u0027s config change will not be rejected\n* \"con\" in project A will start failing to resolve, which will block future config updates in project A.\n\nThis doesn\u0027t seem good though; I think a better solution is for \"con\" to get removed from the datastore, so it no longer shows up. I could also make the same change for consoles that get rejected for other reasons during the config update. I\u0027ll work on that tomorrow (assuming you agree).\n\nNot sure I really understand your final question, but no, there\u0027s no such ACL that I know of.",
