      "writtenOn": "2020-07-01T18:00:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Having con be removed from datastore in the meantime sounds right to me (maybe some special tombstone so milo can render the console as \"there was a console here, but it\u0027s been removed from otherProject\"?).  That said, I think we do still want to reject new updates referencing consoles that don\u0027t exist (i.e. project A shouldn\u0027t be able to refer to consoles that don\u0027t exist; referring to \"otherProject/mainConsoul\" should be an error.)\n\nACL was just in case B\u0027s config updates would be blocked; If B cannot be blocked by A, then B doesn\u0027t need to grant any particular permissions to A.",
