    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "785d6adb_b615aca5",
        "filename": "milo/common/config.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 631,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-01T18:00:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Datastore transactions which read/write independent entities groups are entirely independent.\n\nThe current maximum number of entity groups which can be be touched in a single transaction is 25 though.\n\nIf we KNOW that nothing else is writing to these entity groups, then _technically_ the most efficient way would be to group all of these into batches of 25 entity groups, then execute the batches in parallel. The downside is that each entity group has a maximum write rate of 1qps, and if something else IS poking at these entity groups, then the entire transaction batch needs to be retried.\n\nIMO, the best (and most \u0027logically correct\u0027) way would be to just do each per-project transaction in parallel. There\u0027s no reason to require that two projects are updated simultaneously, so there\u0027s no application level requirement to batch them (just silly datastore RPC overhead optimization potential, imo too micro to matter).",
      "parentUuid": "cabeb612_36bac4f5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 631,
        "startChar": 53,
        "endLine": 631,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "8522ab2d7eb4ba983c65bf2042e8956a503233bf",
